Author: Kari L. Jordan Published: April 2017

THIS IS JUST A DRAFT

A PDF of the survey questions, the data used in this analysis, and full R code are located on the public-survey-info repo on GitHub. Feel free to use the data and tell us about your findings.

Likert Items

Using the Likert package, the following chart is an analysis of learner responses to the statements above. The code chunk is shown once here, and hidden for all subsequent plots.

cols_with_Agree <- map_lgl(data, ~`%in%`("Agree", .x))
data_agree <-  data[ , cols_with_Agree]

data_agree <- map_if(data_agree, 
                     is.character, 
                     as.factor)
# This code worked yesterday to order the likert items and now it's not working.
#for(i in seq_along(data_agree)) {
#                data_agree[[i]] <- factor(data_agree[[i]], levels=order)
#}

title <- "Learner Perception of Carpentry Workshops"
data_agree_likert <-  likert(as.data.frame(data_agree))
theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

plot(data_agree_likert) + ggtitle(title)
